
1. The Central African Republic can be abbreviated as the C.A.R.
2. This is a landlocked country, meaning there is no direct passageway
to the sea/ocean from or inside this country.
3. The Central African Republic has been settled in the area for 
at least 8,000 years, as there have been 8,000 year-old flint and
quartz tools found in the nation.
4. This nation gained its independence in 1960. The Central African
Republic's first president was David Dacko.
5. The Central African Republic is one of the few countries deemed not
fit for travel due to the high crime rate and activities of armed forces.
6.